{{Lunisolar November}}
'''November 26''' is the 26th day of month {{ill|November (Lunisolar)|ja|11月 (旧暦)|lt=November (Shimotsuki)}}, the 11th month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar}}. Its {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜}} day is {{ill|Shakkō|ja|赤口}}.

== Events ==
* [[Ōtoku]] 3rd year ({{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano}} [[1087]] {{ill|January 3|ja|1月3日}}) – In this year, Emperor [[Hakuba Tennō|白河天皇]] abdicated in favor of his young successor, who then began his reign as an incumbent emperor while serving as a retired emperor (上皇) during the subsequent period of cloistered rule.
* [[Chishō]] 4th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano}} [[1180]] {{ill|December 14|ja|12月14日}}) – Taira no Kiyomori returned the capital from Fukuhara to Heian-kyō.
* [[Shōgen (Japan)|Shōgen]] 1st year ({{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano}} [[1260]] {{ill|January 9|ja|1月9日}}) – Emperor Go-Fukakusa was forced by his father, former Emperor Go-Saga, to cede the throne to his younger brother, leading to a split in the imperial line between the Daikakuji and Jōmyōin houses.
* {{ill|Bunroku|ja|文禄}} 2nd year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦}} [[1594]] {{ill|January 17|ja|1月17日}}) – By imperial command, the printed edition of the "Kobun-kōkyō" (an edict of Keichō) was produced; this marked the production of Japan’s first wooden movable type printed book.
== Births ==
