kyō" (an edict of Keichō) was produced; this marked the production of Japan’s first wooden movable type printed book. == Births == * [[An'ei]] 9th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=|qq=draft}} [[1780]] {{ill|December 21|ja|12月21日|qq=|qq=draft}}) – {{ill|Kurozumi Sōchū|ja|黒住宗忠|qq=|qq=draft}}, the founder of the Kurozumi school of Confucian thought (died [[1850]]). * [[Tenmei]] 4th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=|qq=draft}} [[1785]] {{ill|January 6|ja|1月6日|qq=|qq=draft}}) – {{ill|Ashiro Hirokun|ja|足代弘訓|qq=|qq=draft}}, a Kokugaku scholar (died [[1856]]). == Deaths == * [[Kōji (Muromachi period)|Kōji]] 1st year ({{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|qq=|qq=draft}} [[1556]] {{ill|January 7|ja|1月7日|qq=|qq=draft}}) – {{ill|Oda Nobuhiro|ja|織田信光|qq=|qq=draft}}, a military commander (born [[1516]]).
