{{Not to be confused with|November 26|qq=November 26}}[[Category:Days of the Japanese Lunisolar Calendar]]<!--why is this category always showing up as 347 members?--> {{afc comment|1=This article as with the other date articles is relatively limited in scope to Japan. Reviewing the translation of this is good and also adding content translated from Chinese and Korean wikipedias will also be good. Both wikipedias are also relatively centered around their own countries for their Lunisolar calendar dates[[User:Immanuelle|Immanuelle]] ([[User talk:Immanuelle|talk]]) 00:16, 28 April 2025 (UTC)}} {{Globalize|article|Japan|date=April 2025}} {{Expand Chinese|1=十一月廿六|topic=hist|date=April 2025}} {{Expand Korean|1=음력 11월 26일|topic=hist|date=April 2025}} {{Lunisolar November|qq=}} '''November 26''' is the 26th day of month {{ill|November (Lunisolar)|ja|11月 (旧暦)|lt=November (Shimotsuki)|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/November (Lunisolar)|qq=}}, the 11th month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=}}. Its {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Rokuyō|qq=}} day is {{ill|Shakkō|ja|赤口|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shakkō|qq=}}.
== Events == * [[Ōtoku]] 3rd year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[1087]] [[:en:January 3|January 3]]) – In this year, Emperor [[Hakuba Tennō|白河天皇]] abdicated in favor of his young successor, who then began his reign as an incumbent emperor while serving as a retired emperor (上皇) during the subsequent period of cloistered rule. * [[Chishō]] 4th year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[1180]] [[:en:December 14|December 14]]) – Taira no Kiyomori returned the capital from Fukuhara to Heian-kyō. * [[Shōgen (Japan)|Shōgen]] 1st year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[1260]] [[:en:January 9|January 9]]) – Emperor Go-Fukakusa was forced by his father, former Emperor Go-Saga, to cede the throne to his younger brother, leading to a split in the imperial line between the Daikakuji and Jōmyōin houses. * [[:en:Bunroku|Bunroku]] 2nd year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1594]] [[:en:January 17|January 17]]) – By imperial command, the printed edition of the "Kobun-kōkyō" (an edict of Keichō) was produced; this marked the production of Japan’s first wooden movable type printed book. == Births == * [[An'ei]] 9th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1780]] [[:en:December 21|December 21]]) – {{ill|Kurozumi Sōchū|ja|黒住宗忠|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kurozumi Sōchū|qq=}}, the founder of the Kurozumi school of Confucian thought (died [[1850]]). * [[Tenmei]] 4th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1785]] [[:en:January 6|January 6]]) – {{ill|Ashiro Hirokun|ja|足代弘訓|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ashiro Hirokun|qq=}}, a Kokugaku scholar (died [[1856]]). == Deaths == * [[Kōji (Muromachi period)|Kōji]] 1st year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[1556]] [[:en:January 7|January 7]]) – {{ill|Oda Nobuhiro|ja|織田信光|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Oda Nobuhiro|qq=}}, a military commander (born [[1516]]).
