== Events == * [[:en:Ōtoku|Ōtoku]] 3rd year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:1087|1087]] [[:en:January 3|January 3]]) – In this year, Emperor [[Hakuba Tennō|白河天皇]] abdicated in favor of his young successor, who then began his reign as an incumbent emperor while serving as a retired emperor (上皇) during the subsequent period of cloistered rule. * [[Chishō]] 4th year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:1180|1180]] [[:en:December 14|December 14]]) – Taira no Kiyomori returned the capital from Fukuhara to Heian-kyō. * [[Shōgen (Japan)|Shōgen]] 1st year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:1260|1260]] [[:en:January 9|January 9]]) – Emperor Go-Fukakusa was forced by his father, former Emperor Go-Saga, to cede the throne to his younger brother, leading to a split in the imperial line between the Daikakuji and Jōmyōin houses. * [[:en:Bunroku|Bunroku]] 2nd year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1594|1594]] [[:en:January 17|January 17]]) – By imperial command, the printed edition of the "Kobun-kōkyō" (an edict of Keichō) was produced; this marked the production of Japan’s first wooden movable type printed book. == Births == * [[:en:An&#39;ei|An&#39;ei]] 9th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1780|1780]] [[:en:December 21|December 21]]) – {{ill|Kurozumi Sōchū|ja|黒住宗忠|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kurozumi Sōchū|qq=|1=Kurozumi Munetada|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11678013}}, the founder of the Kurozumi school of Confucian thought (died [[:en:1850|1850]]). * [[:en:Tenmei|Tenmei]] 4th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1785|1785]] [[:en:January 6|January 6]]) – {{ill|Ashiro Hirokun|ja|足代弘訓|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ashiro Hirokun|qq=|1=Hironori Ajiro|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q6535014}}, a Kokugaku scholar (died [[:en:1856|1856]]). == Deaths == * [[:en:Kōji (Muromachi period)|Kōji]] 1st year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:1556|1556]] [[:en:January 7|January 7]]) – {{ill|Oda Nobuhiro|ja|織田信光|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Oda Nobuhiro|qq=|1=Oda Nobumitsu|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11608264}}, a military commander (born [[:en:1516|1516]]).
